# ── Documents ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Replace the path below with the absolute path to any PDF on your machine.
# VS Code REST Client supports multipart/form-data with < @path syntax.

### Ingest a PDF (happy path) — requires a valid JWT in @token above
POST {{HostAddress}}/api/documents/ingest
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./sample.pdf
--boundary--

###

### Ingest a plain-text file
POST {{HostAddress}}/api/documents/ingest
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="notes.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

< ./notes.txt
--boundary--

###

### Ingest — missing auth (expects 401)
POST {{HostAddress}}/api/documents/ingest
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./sample.pdf
--boundary--

###

### Ingest — unsupported file type (expects 400)
POST {{HostAddress}}/api/documents/ingest
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="image.png"
Content-Type: image/png

< ./image.png
--boundary--

###

# ── Semantic Search ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Search — RAG pipeline overview (top 5 most relevant chunks)
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/documents/search?q=What is the RAG pipeline flow?&topK=5
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Search — technology stack
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/documents/search?q=What technologies are used in this project?&topK=3
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Search — authentication and security
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/documents/search?q=How does JWT authentication work?&topK=3
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Search — missing auth (expects 401)
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/documents/search?q=RAG pipeline

###

### Search — missing query param (expects 400)
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/documents/search
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Search — topK out of range (expects 400)
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/documents/search?q=architecture&topK=50
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ── Health ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Health check (public — expects 200)
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/health

###

# ── Documents — List / Status / Delete ───────────────────────────────────────

### List all documents for the authenticated user
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/documents
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Get ingestion status of a specific document (replace with real id)
@documentId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

GET {{HostAddress}}/api/documents/{{documentId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Delete a document + its Qdrant vectors (expects 204)
DELETE {{HostAddress}}/api/documents/{{documentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Delete — missing auth (expects 401)
DELETE {{HostAddress}}/api/documents/{{documentId}}

###

### Delete — unknown id (expects 404)
DELETE {{HostAddress}}/api/documents/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ── Conversations ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Create a new conversation (title is optional)
POST {{HostAddress}}/api/conversations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "RAG pipeline questions"
}

###

### Create conversation — empty title (auto-generated)
POST {{HostAddress}}/api/conversations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### List all conversations for the authenticated user
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/conversations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### List conversations — missing auth (expects 401)
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/conversations

###

# ── Conversations — Messages ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# After creating a conversation above, paste the returned id here:
@conversationId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

### Get message history for a conversation
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/conversations/{{conversationId}}/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Get messages — unknown id (expects 404)
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/conversations/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Send a message — non-streaming RAG response (full JSON)
POST {{HostAddress}}/api/conversations/{{conversationId}}/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "What is the RAG pipeline flow?",
  "topK": 5
}

###

### Send message — missing question (expects 400)
POST {{HostAddress}}/api/conversations/{{conversationId}}/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "",
  "topK": 5
}

###

### Send message — missing auth (expects 401)
POST {{HostAddress}}/api/conversations/{{conversationId}}/messages
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "test"
}

###

### Send message — unknown conversation (expects 404)
POST {{HostAddress}}/api/conversations/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "test"
}

