# ── Chat / SSE Streaming ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The SSE stream endpoint is best tested with curl or a browser EventSource —
# the VS Code REST Client does NOT render SSE events progressively, but it WILL
# receive and display the full chunked response once the stream finishes.
# Recommended curl command:
#   curl -N -H "Authorization: Bearer <token>" \
#        "http://localhost:5087/api/chat/<conversationId>/stream?q=What+is+the+RAG+pipeline%3F"

### SSE stream — happy path
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/chat/{{conversationId}}/stream?q=What is the RAG pipeline flow?&topK=5
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: text/event-stream

###

### SSE stream — different question
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/chat/{{conversationId}}/stream?q=How does JWT authentication work?&topK=3
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: text/event-stream

###

### SSE stream — missing auth (expects 401)
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/chat/{{conversationId}}/stream?q=test

###

### SSE stream — missing query param (expects 400)
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/chat/{{conversationId}}/stream
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### SSE stream — topK out of range (expects 400)
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/chat/{{conversationId}}/stream?q=architecture&topK=50
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### SSE stream — unknown conversation id (expects 404)
GET {{HostAddress}}/api/chat/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001/stream?q=test
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###
